SIMPLE: preventer
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Preventer
<hw>Pre*vent"er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One
who goes before; one who forestalls or anticipates another.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Bacon.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>One who prevents or obstructs; a hinderer; that
which hinders; <as>as, a <ex>preventer</ex> of evils or of
disease</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Naut.)</fld> <def>An auxiliary rope to strengthen a
mast.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><mcol><col><b>Preventer bolts</b></col>, <it>or</it>
<col><b>Preventer plates</b></col></mcol> <fld>(Naut.)</fld>,
<cd>fixtures connected with preventers to re⟦eum⟧nforce other
rigging.</cd> -- <col><b>Preventer stay</b></col>. <fld>(Naut.)</fld>
<cd>Same as <er>Preventer</er>, 3.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Preventingly</ent>⟦br⟧
